A MAN is dead and his girlfriend is in hospital after they were shot in an attempted hijacking on Sunday afternoon. The victim and his girlfriend were sitting in his car in Umbilo, Durban, when they were approached by an armed 25-year-old man. The suspect allegedly shot the couple before fleeing from the scene on foot, but he was arrested a few minutes after the incident. Garrith Jamieson, Rescue Care Paramedics spokesman, said paramedics arrived at the scene to find two people had sustained gunshot wounds. &ldquo;A man in his 30s had sustained a single shot to his upper body. Paramedics assessed him but unfortunately there was nothing they could do as he was dead. A woman in her 20s had a gunshot wound in the lower body and was stabilised before being taken to a nearby hospital.&rdquo; Captain Nqobile Gwala, KZN police spokeswoman, said a brave cop chased the armed suspect and managed to arrest him minutes after the shooting. &ldquo;The suspect will appear in the Durban Magistrates Court soon on charges of murder, attempted murder and possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition.&rdquo; Gwala confirmed the man and woman were sitting in a car when the incident took place. &ldquo;The victim was in his vehicle on Ferguson Road with his girlfriend when they were attacked and an attempted hijacking took place. &ldquo;The suspect allegedly shot and killed the driver and wounded the girlfriend.&rdquo; She said the suspect was bust on nearby Brand Road after fleeing the scene.